Use Hospital_Compare IF EXISTS (SELECT * FROM sys.objects WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID(N'[dbo].[tbl_HAI_Summary]') AND type in (N'U')) DROP TABLE [dbo].[tbl_HAI_Summary]
Create table tbl_HAI_Summary ( Hospital varchar(500) ,City varchar(100) ,State varchar(50) ,ZIP_Code bigint ,County varchar(100) ,Measure varchar(500) ,Score float ,Percentile float)
Insert into tbl_HAI_Summary ( Hospital ,City ,State ,ZIP_Code ,County ,Measure ,Score ,Percentile ) Select [Hospital Name] ,[City] ,[State] ,[ZIP Code] ,[County Name], [Measure Name], [Score], 1- PERCENT_RANK() OVER (Partition by [Measure ID] order by [Score]) as Percentile FROM [Hospital_Compare].[dbo].[tbl_All_Measures_By_Hospital] as a inner join [Hospital_Compare].[dbo].[tbl_Hospitals] as b on a.[Provider ID] = b.[Provider ID] Where [Measure ID] like '%SIR' and Score is not null
